---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { readFileSync, existsSync } from 'node:fs';
import { resolve, dirname } from 'node:path';
import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

interface OODJson {
  events: Array<{
    eventId: string;
    eventName: string;
    startDate?: string;
    trueState?: string;
    entropy: number;
    maxProb: number;
    jaccardDistance: number;
    correct: boolean;
    bestRank: number | null;
  }>;
  trainingEntropiesSorted: number[];
  percentiles: { p10: number; p25: number; p50: number; p75: number; p85: number; p90: number; p95: number; p99: number };
  pearsonEntropyJaccard: number;
  meanEntropyCorrect: number;
  meanEntropyWrong: number;
  generatedAt: string;
}

const here = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));
const cachePath = resolve(here, '..', '..', '..', '.cache', 'ood-eval.json');
const data: OODJson | null = existsSync(cachePath)
  ? JSON.parse(readFileSync(cachePath, 'utf8'))
  : null;

// Build histograms client-side at build time.
const HIST_BINS = 30;
const lnK = Math.log(10); // max entropy for K=10

function histogram(values: number[], min: number, max: number, bins: number): number[] {
  const out = new Array<number>(bins).fill(0);
  const w = (max - min) / bins;
  for (const v of values) {
    if (!Number.isFinite(v)) continue;
    let i = Math.floor((v - min) / w);
    if (i < 0) i = 0;
    if (i >= bins) i = bins - 1;
    out[i]++;
  }
  return out;
}

const histAll      = data ? histogram(data.events.map((e) => e.entropy), 0, lnK, HIST_BINS) : [];
const histCorrect  = data ? histogram(data.events.filter((e) => e.correct).map((e) => e.entropy), 0, lnK, HIST_BINS) : [];
const histWrong    = data ? histogram(data.events.filter((e) => !e.correct).map((e) => e.entropy), 0, lnK, HIST_BINS) : [];
const histMax = Math.max(1, ...histAll, ...histCorrect, ...histWrong);

// Scatter for entropy × Jaccard
const SCATTER_W = 480;
const SCATTER_H = 280;
const PAD_L = 40, PAD_R = 12, PAD_T = 12, PAD_B = 36;
const innerW = SCATTER_W - PAD_L - PAD_R;
const innerH = SCATTER_H - PAD_T - PAD_B;
function sx(e: number) { return PAD_L + (e / lnK) * innerW; }
function sy(d: number) { return PAD_T + (1 - d) * innerH; }

// Histogram geometry
const H_W = 560;
const H_H = 220;
const HPAD_L = 40, HPAD_R = 12, HPAD_T = 14, HPAD_B = 30;
const hInnerW = H_W - HPAD_L - HPAD_R;
const hInnerH = H_H - HPAD_T - HPAD_B;
function hx(i: number) { return HPAD_L + (i / HIST_BINS) * hInnerW; }
function hy(c: number) { return HPAD_T + (1 - c / histMax) * hInnerH; }
const barW = hInnerW / HIST_BINS;
---
<Base title="OOD methodology — backtest" wide>
  <p class="kicker">Research</p>
  <h1>Out-of-distribution detection</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Two complementary methodologies for "is this event weird enough
    that I should treat the engine's prediction with extra caution?"
    <strong>Jaccard nearest-neighbor</strong> catches structural
    novelty — events whose feature set doesn't match anything in
    the training corpus. <strong>Calibrated-softmax entropy</strong>
    catches model uncertainty — events where the engine itself can't
    decide between candidates. They're orthogonal signals; we expose
    both.
  </p>

  {!data ? (
    <p class="reading">
      <strong>No cached result.</strong> Run <code>pnpm run eval-ood</code>
      from <code>site/</code> to populate <code>.cache/ood-eval.json</code>,
      then rebuild.
    </p>
  ) : (
    <>
      <p class="meta">
        Generated {data.generatedAt} · n = {data.events.length} held-out events
        scored via LOO with NB · calibrated at T = 2.0 (the fitted
        attribution-engine temperature).
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>Headline finding</h2>
        <div class="stat-grid">
          <div class="stat"><strong>{data.meanEntropyCorrect.toFixed(2)}</strong>mean entropy on correct predictions (nats)</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>{data.meanEntropyWrong.toFixed(2)}</strong>mean entropy on incorrect predictions</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>{(data.meanEntropyWrong / data.meanEntropyCorrect).toFixed(2)}×</strong>entropy gap</div>
          <div class="stat"><strong>r = {data.pearsonEntropyJaccard.toFixed(3)}</strong>Pearson(entropy, Jaccard distance)</div>
        </div>
        <p class="reading">
          The entropy gap ({(data.meanEntropyWrong / data.meanEntropyCorrect).toFixed(2)}×)
          is the empirical signal that supports using softmax entropy
          as an abstain-or-flag mechanism: when the engine's entropy
          is in the high tail, it's correct {((100 * data.events.filter((e) => e.entropy > data.percentiles.p85 && e.correct).length) / Math.max(1, data.events.filter((e) => e.entropy > data.percentiles.p85).length)).toFixed(0)}%
          of the time (above the 85th-percentile threshold) versus
          {' '}{((100 * data.events.filter((e) => e.entropy <= data.percentiles.p85 && e.correct).length) / Math.max(1, data.events.filter((e) => e.entropy <= data.percentiles.p85).length)).toFixed(0)}%
          below. The orthogonality between entropy and Jaccard
          distance (r = {data.pearsonEntropyJaccard.toFixed(3)}) means
          neither methodology subsumes the other — they catch
          different OOD modes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Training-event entropy distribution</h2>
        <p>
          The empirical training distribution. Vertical lines mark
          the percentile thresholds AUSPEX uses to classify a query
          event as in-distribution, borderline, or OOD. Maximum
          possible entropy for K=10 candidates is
          ln(10) = {lnK.toFixed(3)} nats (uniform distribution); the
          right edge of the histogram approaches this limit.
        </p>
        <figure class="chart">
          <svg viewBox={`0 0 ${H_W} ${H_H}`} width={H_W} height={H_H} role="img" aria-label="Histogram of LOO entropies">
            {/* y-axis baseline */}
            <line x1={HPAD_L} y1={HPAD_T + hInnerH} x2={HPAD_L + hInnerW} y2={HPAD_T + hInnerH} stroke="var(--ctp-overlay0)" />
            <line x1={HPAD_L} y1={HPAD_T} x2={HPAD_L} y2={HPAD_T + hInnerH} stroke="var(--ctp-overlay0)" />

            {/* Bars: stacked (correct = green, wrong = red) */}
            {histAll.map((_, i) => {
              const c = histCorrect[i];
              const w = histWrong[i];
              const cH = (c / histMax) * hInnerH;
              const wH = (w / histMax) * hInnerH;
              const yC = HPAD_T + hInnerH - cH;
              const yW = yC - wH;
              return (
                <g>
                  {c > 0 && <rect x={hx(i) + 1} y={yC} width={barW - 2} height={cH} fill="var(--ctp-green)" opacity="0.7" />}
                  {w > 0 && <rect x={hx(i) + 1} y={yW} width={barW - 2} height={wH} fill="var(--ctp-red)" opacity="0.7" />}
                </g>
              );
            })}

            {/* Percentile threshold lines */}
            {[
              { p: data.percentiles.p50, label: 'median', color: 'var(--ctp-blue)' },
              { p: data.percentiles.p85, label: '85% (borderline)', color: 'var(--ctp-yellow)' },
              { p: data.percentiles.p95, label: '95% (OOD)',        color: 'var(--ctp-red)'    },
            ].map(({ p, label, color }) => (
              <g>
                <line x1={HPAD_L + (p / lnK) * hInnerW} y1={HPAD_T} x2={HPAD_L + (p / lnK) * hInnerW} y2={HPAD_T + hInnerH} stroke={color} stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3 3" />
                <text x={HPAD_L + (p / lnK) * hInnerW} y={HPAD_T - 2} text-anchor="middle" class="h-label" style={`fill: ${color};`}>{label}</text>
              </g>
            ))}

            {/* x-axis ticks */}
            {[0, 0.5, 1, 1.5, 2].map((t) => (
              t < lnK && (
                <g>
                  <line x1={HPAD_L + (t / lnK) * hInnerW} y1={HPAD_T + hInnerH} x2={HPAD_L + (t / lnK) * hInnerW} y2={HPAD_T + hInnerH + 3} stroke="var(--ctp-overlay0)" />
                  <text x={HPAD_L + (t / lnK) * hInnerW} y={HPAD_T + hInnerH + 14} text-anchor="middle" class="h-tick">{t.toFixed(1)}</text>
                </g>
              )
            ))}
            <text x={HPAD_L + (lnK / lnK) * hInnerW} y={HPAD_T + hInnerH + 14} text-anchor="middle" class="h-tick">{lnK.toFixed(2)}</text>

            {/* axis labels */}
            <text x={HPAD_L + hInnerW / 2} y={H_H - 4} text-anchor="middle" class="h-axis">entropy (nats)</text>
            <text x={12} y={HPAD_T + hInnerH / 2} text-anchor="middle" class="h-axis" transform={`rotate(-90 12 ${HPAD_T + hInnerH / 2})`}>n events</text>
          </svg>
          <figcaption>
            <span class="leg"><span class="sw" style="background: var(--ctp-green);"></span>engine got rank-1 correct</span>
            <span class="leg"><span class="sw" style="background: var(--ctp-red);"></span>engine got rank-1 wrong</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Entropy × Jaccard distance</h2>
        <p>
          Scatter of held-out events, colored by correctness. If the
          two OOD methodologies were redundant, points would cluster
          on a diagonal; instead they fill the plane, confirming the
          methodologies catch different OOD modes. Correct events
          (green) concentrate in the bottom-left (low entropy, low
          Jaccard distance — "the engine confidently identifies a
          familiar pattern"); wrong events (red) fan out across the
          rest of the plane.
        </p>
        <figure class="chart">
          <svg viewBox={`0 0 ${SCATTER_W} ${SCATTER_H}`} width={SCATTER_W} height={SCATTER_H} role="img" aria-label="Entropy vs Jaccard scatter">
            {/* gridlines */}
            {[0.25, 0.5, 0.75].map((p) => (
              <g>
                <line x1={PAD_L} y1={PAD_T + p * innerH} x2={PAD_L + innerW} y2={PAD_T + p * innerH} stroke="var(--ctp-surface0)" stroke-dasharray="2 3" />
                <text x={PAD_L - 6} y={PAD_T + p * innerH + 3} text-anchor="end" class="h-tick">{(1 - p).toFixed(2)}</text>
              </g>
            ))}
            {[0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1].map((p) => (
              <g>
                <line x1={PAD_L + p * innerW} y1={PAD_T} x2={PAD_L + p * innerW} y2={PAD_T + innerH} stroke="var(--ctp-surface0)" stroke-dasharray="2 3" />
                <text x={PAD_L + p * innerW} y={PAD_T + innerH + 14} text-anchor="middle" class="h-tick">{(p * lnK).toFixed(2)}</text>
              </g>
            ))}
            {/* axis baselines */}
            <line x1={PAD_L} y1={PAD_T} x2={PAD_L} y2={PAD_T + innerH} stroke="var(--ctp-overlay0)" />
            <line x1={PAD_L} y1={PAD_T + innerH} x2={PAD_L + innerW} y2={PAD_T + innerH} stroke="var(--ctp-overlay0)" />
            {/* points */}
            {data.events.map((e) => (
              <circle
                cx={sx(e.entropy).toFixed(1)}
                cy={sy(e.jaccardDistance).toFixed(1)}
                r="2.5"
                fill={e.correct ? 'var(--ctp-green)' : 'var(--ctp-red)'}
                opacity="0.45"
              />
            ))}
            {/* axis labels */}
            <text x={PAD_L + innerW / 2} y={SCATTER_H - 4} text-anchor="middle" class="h-axis">entropy (nats)</text>
            <text x={10} y={PAD_T + innerH / 2} text-anchor="middle" class="h-axis" transform={`rotate(-90 10 ${PAD_T + innerH / 2})`}>Jaccard distance</text>
          </svg>
        </figure>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Methodology</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <strong>Jaccard nearest-neighbor (existing).</strong>
            Feature-set similarity max over training events.
            1 − max-similarity = distance. Hand-tuned thresholds
            (0.55 borderline, 0.75 OOD) selected to match the LOO
            error-rate transition. Catches structural OOD — events
            whose features don't co-occur in any training event.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Calibrated-softmax entropy (Hendrycks &amp; Gimpel 2016).</strong>
            Softmax the top-10 NB log-scores with temperature scaling
            (T = {(2.0).toFixed(1)}, fitted via the engine-wide
            calibration); take Shannon entropy. High entropy means
            the engine is spread thin across many candidates.
            Thresholds are <em>data-derived</em>: the 85th and 95th
            percentiles of the training-event entropy distribution
            give the borderline / OOD cutoffs. No hand-tuning
            beyond the percentile choice.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>How to use both.</strong> A query event is
            classified as <em>in-distribution</em> only if both
            methodologies agree it's in-distribution. If either
            flags borderline / OOD, the engine's prediction should
            carry a confidence caveat. The two signals are orthogonal
            (r = {data.pearsonEntropyJaccard.toFixed(3)}), so the
            intersection is a stricter test than either alone.
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p class="reading">
          <strong>Caveat.</strong> The training distribution used
          here is computed from a single LOO pass. For thesis-grade
          reporting, the right protocol is the same stratified k-fold
          we use for the stacker (each event participates in eval
          exactly once with its entropy computed from a model that
          never saw it). The single-LOO distribution is a close
          approximation but should be re-computed under k-fold for
          the snapshot. See <a href="/research/stacked-eval">/research/stacked-eval</a>
          for the k-fold pattern.
        </p>
      </section>
    </>
  )}
</Base>

<style>
  .meta { color: var(--ctp-subtext0); font-size: 0.9375rem; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }
  .stat-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .stat {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.125rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    background: var(--ctp-mantle);
    border: 1px solid var(--ctp-surface0);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--ctp-subtext1);
  }
  .stat strong { font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--ctp-text); font-weight: 600; }
  .reading {
    background: var(--ctp-mantle);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--ctp-blue);
    padding: 0.625rem 0.875rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    margin: 0.75rem 0;
  }
  .chart {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem;
    background: var(--ctp-mantle);
    border: 1px solid var(--ctp-surface0);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }
  .chart figcaption {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ctp-subtext0);
  }
  .leg { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.375rem; }
  .sw { display: inline-block; width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 2px; }
  .h-tick {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    fill: var(--ctp-overlay1);
  }
  .h-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .h-axis {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    fill: var(--ctp-subtext0);
  }
  ol li { margin: 0.5rem 0; }
</style>
